                                    <p>
                                  
                                        
                                        Natural Product Communications (NPC), launched in 2006, provides a major
                                        venue for rapid publication of high quality natural products research, including
                                        organic, medicinal, pharmaceutical, bioorganic, analytical, theoretical, biotechnological
                                        and chemotaxonomic aspects. We are delighted that NPC has made such a good start
                                        and has attracted the attention of scientists world wide, as indicated by submissions
                                        and the web statistics. This has only been possible due to the large number of high
                                        quality submissions and the tremendous efforts of the reviewers. We are very grateful
                                        to all the authors who have submitted such high quality work to the journal and
                                        the reviewers for dealing with the manuscripts so quickly. <br /><br />
                                        
                                        During 2007 we had one
                                        thematic issue on ‘Bioactive essential oils’ and three honorarium issues to commemorate
                                        the birthdays of two internationally renowned natural product researchers. The March
                                        and April issues were to celebrate the 65th birthday of Professor Yoshinori Asakawa,
                                        and the October issue the 75th birthday of Professor Tom J. Mabry. We thank all
                                        those authors who contributed papers for these issues and the reviewers, all of
                                        whom responded to a short and challenging timetable. We are pleased to mention that
                                        NPC will be proud to recognize other eminent scientists by dedicating an issue in
                                        their honour, and suggestions will be welcomed. <br /><br />
                                        
                                        We are committed to placing this
                                        journal at the forefront for the dissemination of novel and exciting natural products
                                        research. We should like to remind all prospective authors that NPC does not have
                                        a page restriction, although we strongly encourage them to present their results
                                        in an even number of pages. Technical details of lesser priority should preferably
                                        be included in ‘supporting information’ rather than in the main text. We look forward
                                        to receiving your submissions and to receiving feedback. <br /><br />
                                        
                                        For the information of
                                        our authors and readers, we have to announce some changes to the Editorial Board
                                        and the Editorial Board of Advisors for 2008. Professor Dr Ernest Haslinger, Institute
                                        of Pharmaceutical Chemistry, University of Graz, Austria has been an editor from
                                        the time of inception of the journal. Due to his retirement, he has expressed a
                                        wish to step down also from his editorial role. His high level of commitment and
                                        expertise will be missed, and the editors and publisher thank him for his many valuable
                                        contributions to the journal. Leaving the Editorial Board of Advisors are Professors
                                        Bruno Botta, Ioanna Chinou, Chun-Nan Lin and Rachel Mata. We thank all of them for
                                        their support. We are, however, pleased to report that as of January 2008, Professor
                                        William N. Setzer, Department of Chemistry, University of Alabama in Huntsville,
                                        Huntsville, Alabama, USA will be joining the Editorial Board, having previously
                                        been a member of the Editorial Board of Advisors. His expertise and experience,
                                        particularly in the field of essential oils, will be most welcome. Professors Viqar
                                        Uddin Ahmad, Giovanni Appendino, Maurizio Bruno and Karen Valent-Vetschera will
                                        be joining the Editorial Advisory Board. We welcome them all and look forward to
                                        working with them. <br /><br />
                                        
